John Prine’s 50-year career had taken him from the folk clubs of Chicago to sold-out venues in London, Australia, and beyond.
Prine joked about his immobility, saying, “OK, now we’re coming to the encore,” because he couldn’t easily leave the stage.
Prine was feeding off the vibe and just having a blast.”“He might as well have danced off the stage,” says Fiona.
Every summer, the Prine family would drive there for huge family reunions.
While the Prine family cannot have a public funeral right now, they are finding ways to celebrate him.